'''冰棒'''是指由水、果汁、糖、牛乳等混合搅拌冷冻而成的一種长条形，中有细棍的[[冰品|冰品]]。

== 作法 ==
將糖等[[調味料|調味料]]、[[香料|香料]]與[[色素|色素]]加入水、果汁或是牛奶中，放入圓柱型的製冰盒中，並在中央處插入長軸（通常是木棒或[[塑膠|塑膠]]製長軸）並[[冷凍|冷凍]]結冰即成冰棒。有些[[固體|固體]]的食材也經常被作為冰棒的原料之一，像是果肉、[[紅豆|紅豆]]、[[綠豆|綠豆]]等。

另外也有些冰棒會在結冰之後，再淋上[[熔化|熔化]]的[[巧克力|巧克力]]或[[黃油|奶油]]覆蓋在其表面使其[[凝固|凝固]]，增加冰棒的口感。

==歷史==
<blockquote>早在1872年，羅斯與羅賓斯二人就開始售賣一種插在棍子上的冷凍水果甜點，稱作“Hokey-Pokey”。<ref name="Pediatrics" >{{cite web|url=http://pediatrics.aappublications.org/content/55/1/29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170511204922/http://pediatrics.aappublications.org/content/55/1/29|dead-url=yes|archive-date=2017-05-11|title=WHO INVENTED THE POPSICLE?|author=Paul Dickson|date=2017-05-11|website=American Academy of Pediatrics|via=archive.org|quote=January 1975, VOLUME 55  ISSUE 1|access-date=2018-11-03}}</ref></blockquote>

1923年，來自美國[[舊金山|舊金山]]的弗朗西斯·威廉·“弗蘭克”·埃珀森<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.familytreenow.com/records/genealogy/epperson/frank|title=Frank Epperson Family Tree - 100% Free Genealogy & Family History Records|website=familytreenow.com|access-date=2018-11-03|archive-date=2021-06-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210602212823/https://www.familytreenow.com/records/genealogy/epperson/frank|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>[http://www.legacy.com/obituaries/auburnjournal/obituary.aspx?n=mae-ross-epperson&pid=175259405 Mae Epperson Obituary - Auburn, CA] {{Wayback|url=http://www.legacy.com/obituaries/auburnjournal/obituary.aspx?n=mae-ross-epperson&pid=175259405 |date=20210603130043 }}  Auburn Journal</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.californiabirthindex.org/birth/francis_w_epperson_born_1917_392585|title=Francis W Epperson, Born 10/27/1917 in California - CaliforniaBirthIndex.org|website=californiabirthindex.org|access-date=2018-11-03|archive-date=2021-06-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210602214039/https://www.californiabirthindex.org/birth/francis_w_epperson_born_1917_392585|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>[https://www.findagrave.com/memorial/29769269/francis-william-epperson Francis William "Frank" Epperson (1894-1983)] {{Wayback|url=https://www.findagrave.com/memorial/29769269/francis-william-epperson |date=20210603041406 }} - Find A Grave Memorial</ref>在獲得“凍冰棍”（Frozen ice on a stick）的專利許可後，冰棒就此普及。<ref name="marks-2012">{{cite web | url=http://www.collectorsweekly.com/articles/the-cold-hard-truth-about-popsicles/ | title=The cold, hard truth about popsicles | website=[[Collectors_Weekly|Collectors Weekly]] | date=2012-08-15 | author=Ben Marks | access-date=2021-05-30 | archive-date=2021-06-21 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210621045342/https://www.collectorsweekly.com/articles/the-cold-hard-truth-about-popsicles/ | dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://tsdr.uspto.gov/#caseNumber=71181614&caseType=SERIAL_NO&searchType=statusSearch|title=Trademark Status & Document Retrieval|website=tsdr.uspto.gov|access-date=2018-06-27|archive-date=2013-05-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130511081924/http://tsdr.uspto.gov/#caseNumber=71181614&caseType=SERIAL_NO&searchType=statusSearch|dead-url=no}}</ref>

埃珀森自稱他於1905年做出了第一支冰棒，那時他只有11歲。<ref name="Pediatrics" />在一個寒冷的夜晚，他不小心把檸檬蘇打水和攪拌棒遺忘在門廊，後來這個故事還印在了冰棒盒上。長大後的埃珀森在[[奧克蘭_(加利福尼亞州)|奧克蘭]]生活，擔任檸檬水銷售員。<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ozy.com/flashback/the-frozen-mistake-that-made-a-fortune/79667|title=The Frozen Mistake That Made a Fortune|first=Laura|last=Elizabeth|website=ozy.com|access-date=November 3, 2018|archive-date=2021-06-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210603060526/https://www.ozy.com/flashback/the-frozen-mistake-that-made-a-fortune/79667/|dead-url=no}}</ref>1922年，埃珀森在一家房地產公司擔任經紀人，在一次消防員舞會上，他將冰棒推介給在座的消防員。<ref name="frank-epperson-89">{{cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/1983/10/27/obituaries/frank-epperson-89-inventor-of-popsicle-dies-in-california.html|title=Frank Epperson, 89, Inventor Of Popsicle, Dies in California|last=AP|website=nytimes.com|access-date=November 3, 2018|archive-date=2018-09-21|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180921001808/https://www.nytimes.com/1983/10/27/obituaries/frank-epperson-89-inventor-of-popsicle-dies-in-california.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://newspaperarchive.com/burlington-daily-times-news-oct-25-1983-p-5/|title=Burlington Daily Times News Archives, Oct 25, 1983, p. 5|date=October 25, 1983|website=newspaperarchive.com|access-date=November 3, 2018|archive-date=2021-06-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210603224518/https://newspaperarchive.com/burlington-daily-times-news-oct-25-1983-p-5/|dead-url=no}}</ref><!-- Burlington Daily Times News Archives, October 25, 1983, p. 5  - The family will be at Sharpe Memorial Chapel tonight from 7 until 8 Popsicle inventor Frank W. Epperson dead FREMONT, Calif. (AP) — Frank ... --><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.buffalospree.com/Buffalo-Spree/August-2012/What-We-Want-Artisan-pops/|title=What We Want: Artisan pops|website=buffalospree.com|access-date=November 3, 2018|archive-date=2020-07-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200728055030/http://www.buffalospree.com/Buffalo-Spree/August-2012/What-We-Want-Artisan-pops/|dead-url=yes}}</ref>而這一產品很快受到市場的歡迎；1923年，時年29歲的埃珀森獲得“Epsicle”冰棒的專利，次年又取得“所有手持冷凍甜點及冰棒棒糖”的專利。後來，他在{{tsl|en|Nepture Beach (California)|海王星海灘 (加利福尼亞州)|海王星海灘}}主題公園正式推出七款水果風味的Epsicle冰棒<ref name="frank-epperson-89"/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ideafinder.com/history/inventions/popsicle.htm|title=Popsicle History - Invention of the Popsicle|first=Phil|last=Ament|website=ideafinder.com|access-date=November 3, 2018|archive-date=2007-05-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070512032337/http://www.ideafinder.com/history/inventions/popsicle.htm|dead-url=no}}</ref>，以“冰凍棒棒糖”或“棒棒飲料”為名販售。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.downtownexpress.com/2017/07/19/the-first-cold-war-popsicle-vs-good-humor/|title=The first Cold War: Popsicle vs. Good Humor - DOWNTOWN EXPRESS|website=downtownexpress.com|access-date=November 3, 2018|archive-date=2020-10-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201005222828/http://www.downtownexpress.com/2017/07/19/the-first-cold-war-popsicle-vs-good-humor/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=CecCHiI95dYC&q=Epperson&pg=PA137|title=The 1920s|first1=Kathleen Morgan|last1=Drowne|first2=Patrick|last2=Huber|first3=Associate Professor of History Patrick Huber|last3=Dr|date=November 3, 2018|publisher=Greenwood Publishing Group|access-date=November 3, 2018|via=Google Books|isbn=9780313320132|archive-date=2021-06-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210616233613/https://books.google.com/books?id=CecCHiI95dYC&q=Epperson&pg=PA137|dead-url=no}}</ref>

幾年後，埃珀森將冰棒的發明權和{{tsl|en|Popsicle|Popsicle}}商標所有權賣給了[[紐約|紐約]]的喬洛公司。<ref name="marks-2012" /><ref name="frank-epperson-89"/>

